1. All source code lives in phase2/StreamList/src/
2. Screens live in src/screens/
3. Shared components live in src/components/common/
4. Screen-specific components live in src/components/[screen-name]/
5. All custom hooks live in src/hooks/
6. All API functions live in src/api/movies.ts
7. Navigation param types live in src/navigation/types.ts
8. All API calls must go through src/api/client.ts only. Never import axios directly in hooks, screens or components.
9. All API endpoint functions live in src/api/movies.ts only. Never call TMDB endpoints directly from hooks or components.
10. The TMDB access token must never appear in any file other than .env
11. Every screen fetches data exclusively through a custom hook. No inline useEffect + fetch inside screen components.
12. Every custom hook must return this exact shape: { data, loading, error, refetch }. No deviations from this interface.
13. All color values must come from src/theme/colors.ts. No hardcoded hex values anywhere in component or screen files.
14. All spacing values must come from src/theme/spacing.ts. No hardcoded pixel values in StyleSheet.
15. All typography styles must come from src/theme/typography.ts. No hardcoded fontSize or fontFamily values in components.
16. Never use pure white (#FFFFFF) for any text — use colors.on_surface.
17. Never use a solid 1px border to define sections or containers. All boundaries are created through background color shifts or spacing alone. This is a hard rule with no exceptions.
18. All styles must use StyleSheet.create only. No inline style props anywhere — style={{ }} is not allowed.
19. No third party UI libraries — no React Native Paper, Elements, or any pre-built component library.
20. No NativeWind, Styled Components or any CSS-in-JS library.
21. Strict TypeScript throughout — no any types permitted.
22. All TMDB API response shapes must have interfaces in src/api/types.ts.
23. All navigation params must be typed in src/navigation/types.ts. No untyped navigation.navigate() calls anywhere.
24. Do not install any new npm package without explicitly asking first.
25. Do not modify the navigation structure without explicitly asking first.
26. Do not modify files outside the current task scope.
27. Watchlist state must only be accessed through src/store/watchlistStore.ts. No local watchlist state in screens or components.
28. Only Zustand is permitted for global state. No Redux, MobX or any other state library.
29. Use colors.surface_bright for all pressed and active states on dark cards.
30. The hero card on Home screen occupies significantly more width than regular cards — asymmetry is intentional, do not make all cards equal width.
31. Use spacing tokens from src/theme/spacing.ts to signal section boundaries. Never use borders or dividers between sections.
32. Use colors.on_surface_variant for all secondary metadata text such as year, genre, rating and subtitles.
33. Never use dividers or separators between list items or carousel items.